The National Assembly Election Petition Tribunal sitting in Bauchi State has nullified the election of Abdulkadir Umar Sarki, the member representing Katagum Federal Constituency. Sarki was declared winner of the election on the platform of the Peoples Redemption Party (PRP) in the last National Assembly election. Ibrahim Mohammed Baba of the All Progressives Congress (APC) had filed a petition challenging the declaration of Sarki as winner of the election. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY In a unanimous judgment delivered yesterday, the three-man panel presided over by Justice Bello Tukur, nullified the election on the grounds that the elections ought to have been declared inconclusive as there were cancellation of results in seven polling units. According to the tribunal, the number of registered voters in the cancelled polling units exceeded the margin of lead between the candidate returned as elected and the runner up. The tribunal, therefore, ordered for a rerun election and withdrawal of the certificate of return issued to the member earlier returned by INEC as winner. Tribunal nullifies Kashamu, six others’ election in Ogun Nasarawa: Tribunal nullifies APC’s Dahiru election Bauchi: Senatorial candidate tenders evidence against Bulkachuwa’s victory Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin